# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore it.
#   For an application, you might want to share it.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#1173, it is a recommended include Pipfile.lock in git.
#   However, if you are working on a system library you can still ignore it.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Poetry uses poetry.lock to ensure reproducible builds.
#   It is recommended to commit poetry.lock but you can ignore it if needed.
#poetry.lock

